From 4cbb7a2876337d82784a576217dc02f8d4133a67 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nagarajan Maran <nmaran@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 4 Sep 2025 12:34:08 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] QSDK:CP:wifi:ath12k: Add WAR to handle non-assoc
 link's assoc failure

Prevent firmware crash caused by non-associated link's association
failure in WDS STA side.

In previous design, ath12k_mac_op_unassign_vif_chanctx handled
vdev stop and delete. With the latest package upgrade, this is now
split: ath12k_mac_op_change_sta_links handles stop, and
ath12k_mac_op_change_vif_links handles delete.

When assoc fails for a non-associated link,
ath12k_mac_op_change_sta_links is not invoked, causing vdev to be
deleted without a stop, leading to firmware crash. A workaround was
introduced to activate the failed link and later triggering
ath12k_mac_op_change_sta_links, ensuring proper vdev deletion.
However this link activation, changes the primary link id of the
STA to non-assoc link.

Fix regression where ahsta->primary_link_id is incorrectly set to
non-associated link in two-link WDS STA MLD setup. Prevent crash by
updating primary_link_id in STA vdev, only when selected link has
successful association status. This change is also a workaround and
a full redesign of assoc failure handling in mac80211 and ath12k is
recommended.

Fixes: 823b06947b14 ("UPSTREAM:CP: wifi: mac80211: Handle non-assoc link connection failure")
Patch-dependency:
    306-UPSTREAM-CP-wifi-mac80211-Handle-non-assoc-link-conn.patch

Signed-off-by: Nagarajan Maran <nmaran@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c | 28 +++++++++++++++++++++++----
 1 file changed, 24 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
@@ -12137,7 +12137,7 @@ int ath12k_mac_op_change_sta_links(struc
 	struct ath12k *ar, *tmp_ar;
 	u16 removed_link_map;
 	u8 link_id, tmp_link_id, pri_link_id;
-	int ret;
+	int ret, assoc_status;
 
 	lockdep_assert_wiphy(hw->wiphy);
 
@@ -12196,10 +12196,31 @@ int ath12k_mac_op_change_sta_links(struc
 			pri_link_id =
 				ath12k_mac_ahsta_get_pri_link_id(ahvif, ahsta,
 								 ahsta->links_map);
-			if (pri_link_id == IEEE80211_MLD_MAX_NUM_LINKS)
+			if (pri_link_id == IEEE80211_MLD_MAX_NUM_LINKS) {
 				pri_link_id = ahsta->assoc_link_id;
-
-			ahsta->primary_link_id = pri_link_id;
+				ahsta->primary_link_id = pri_link_id;
+			} else {
+				arvif =
+				wiphy_dereference(hw->wiphy, ahvif->link[pri_link_id]);
+
+				if (vif->type == NL80211_IFTYPE_STATION && arvif &&
+				    !ath12k_mac_is_bridge_vdev(arvif)) {
+					assoc_status =
+					ieee80211_get_link_assoc_status(vif, pri_link_id);
+					/* When the assoc is failed for the selected
+					 * link, then avoid updating that link as primary
+					 */
+					if (assoc_status != 0) {
+						ath12k_err(NULL,
+							   "Selected pri_link_id:%u, retain pri_link_id:%u\n",
+							   pri_link_id,
+							   ahsta->primary_link_id);
+						goto skip_pri_link_selection;
+					}
+				}
+				ahsta->primary_link_id = pri_link_id;
+			}
+skip_pri_link_selection:
 			ath12k_dbg(NULL, ATH12K_DBG_MAC,
 				   "mac ML STA %pM primary link set to %u\n",
 				   sta->addr, ahsta->primary_link_id);
